AFRICAN SWINE FEVER - BURUNDI: (NGOZI) SWINE, OIE
*************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Thu 3 Mar 2016
Source: OIE, WAHID weekly disease information 2016; 29(08) [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=19840


African swine fever, Burundi
----------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 3 Mar 2016 from Dr Deogratias Nsanganiyumwami, [Director Animal Health, Ministry of Agriculture and Livestock], Gitega, Burundi

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 28 Feb 2016
Date of confirmation of the event: 2 Mar 2016
Reason for notification: Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 30 Nov 2015
Causal agent: African swine fever [ASF] virus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced), necropsy
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (2)
Outbreak 1: Gashikanwa, Ngozi
Date of start of the outbreak: 28 Feb 2016
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Swine / 1789 / 15 / 8 / 0 / 0
Affected population: animals affected are from both sexes, of all ages, from local breed and Large White one.

Outbreak 2: Nyamurenza, Ngozi
Date of start of the outbreak: 28 Feb 2016
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Affected animals:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Swine / 2752 / 125 / 98 / 0 / 0
Affected population: animals affected are from both sexes, of all ages, from local breed and Large White one.

Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks: 2
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Destroyed / Slaughtered
Swine / 4541 / 140 / 106 / 0 / 0
Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Swine / 3.08 / 2.33 / 75.71 / 2.33
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: the disease occurred last year [2015] until the month of November in the same and it seems that the virus remained there.

Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; screening; disinfection/disinfestations; no vaccination; no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: no other measures

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreaks can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[During the past few years Burundi has submitted its 6-monthly and annual reports only for the year 2015. No information is available for the years 2013 and 2014.

According to information submitted in their July-December 2015, 6-monthly report, ASF was reported as "present" in the country. 18 outbreaks were reported during this semester. These were located in the provinces of Cibitoke, Kayanza, and Ngozi. See report at http://tinyurl.com/zvvwt8o.

Maps of Burundi can be seen at http://www.nationsonline.org/oneworld/map/burundi_map.htm and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4074647,52256. - Mod.CRD]
